node.text: It’s been a few years of working with @cartier now, and every time is a pinch me moment! To be a part of a global tribe of strong and confident women representing the power of the panthère spirit, a beautiful fragrance created by @mathilde.laurent is truly an honor. If you’d like to discover the fragrance for yourself, be sure to check my “Cartier” highlight and enjoy a gift from Maison Cartier this holiday season 🐆 #PanthèredeCartier #CartierParfums

node.text: TW // suicide 💭 My biggest highlight from 2021 was choosing to confront my darkest demons and work towards healing. I originally shared these in my stories yesterday, but I’m placing them here and creating a highlight as well in the hopes to help more people ❤️

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Lee Litumbe 🇨🇲🇺🇸 on January 03, 2022. May be an image of one or more people, lake, nature, sky and twilight.

Photo by Lee Litumbe 🇨🇲🇺🇸 on January 03, 2022. May be an image of lake, sky and text that says '2021 was one of the most difficult years of my life. I battled depression and anxiety, confronted my deeply buried traumas left from years of abuse in my adolescence paid off my debt and all student loans, and began the journey of true self love and acceptance.'.

Photo by Lee Litumbe 🇨🇲🇺🇸 on January 03, 2022. May be an image of text that says '8 I realized last year that I was performing happiness more than embodying it, so decided to commit to start doing the very deep, unglamorous, and painful work of healing.'.

Photo by Lee Litumbe 🇨🇲🇺🇸 on January 03, 2022. May be an image of ring and text that says 'Something about getting engaged last December brought on the strongest sense of urgency to address all the things i'd spen the past years running away from. Which realized was mostly from myself.'.

Photo by Lee Litumbe 🇨🇲🇺🇸 on January 03, 2022. May be an image of child, lake and text that says 'It was truly hard work reconnecting with my inner child and consoling her. To be completely vulnerable with you, I've attempted suicide twice before in my life. As preteen and in my late teens. Thankfully was not successful, but never really explored those things. Instead,I further escaped into my art, my dreams, and my travels. LENA ۲'.

Photo by Lee Litumbe 🇨🇲🇺🇸 on January 03, 2022. May be an image of flower, tree, outdoors and text that says 'It's not an easy thing to publically share, but it's important forme to remind you that no one has a perfect life. No matter how glamorous a person's life may look. At 33 years old, I'm grateful to finally be in a place of peace. I know this is not your typical yearly highlight of fun photos, but I hope it will inspire you nonetheless. I encourage anyone who is considering therapy to go for it...it has been seriously life changing'.

Photo by Lee Litumbe 🇨🇲🇺🇸 on January 03, 2022. May be an illustration of one or more people and text that says 'I also spent most of last year in a creative rut due to all the things was dealing with personally, and am so happy finally to be on the other side of that. won't do bunch of corny announcements, just know to watch this space ትት2S Dierrς BiKOKT T manicur'.
Photo by Lee Litumbe 🇨🇲🇺🇸 on January 03, 2022. May be an image of lake and text that says 'Heal. You deserve peace, ease, and a soft life.'.

Photo by Lee Litumbe 🇨🇲🇺🇸 on January 03, 2022. May be an image of text that says 'I also want to clarify that my journey with therapy is ongoing. Even though now feel peace, still takes work to maintain and requires me to approach my life with more routine and to develop better habits.'.

Photo shared by Lee Litumbe 🇨🇲🇺🇸 on January 03, 2022 tagging @therapyforblackgirls, @nedratawwab, @the.holistic.psychologist, and @drbeckyatgoodinside. May be an image of text that says 'If you have ever experienceo having suio idal thoughts, please please please reach out to someone, anyone, for help You're not as alone you think you are. will share with you some of my favorite mental health/therapy accounts in the next frame'.
